Concurrency:-
When we are allowed to switch to the tasks but doing only one task at a time then it is concurrency.
Parallelism:-
We are doing all the work at one time


Go routine is the way how we achieve the parallelism.
Threads are managed by OS.(Fixed stack)
Goroutines are managed by go runtime.(Flexible stack)
And since we can fire up more and more apis at a time hence it is very fast in case of go routine
